Work in high-exposure necrosteries includes workers involved with the preparation of bodies of people with confirmed VOCID-19 or suspected of the disease at the time of their death; the risk of exposure of becoming very high if they perform autopsy. Additional engineering controls for these risk groups include isolation rooms for patients with confirmed or suspected VOCID-19, including when aerosol generating procedures are performed.
